# Article URLs

## URL Structure

- **Article pages live at** `/articles/[slug]/` (e.g. `/articles/same-day-tv-installation-los-angeles/`)
- **Content source**: `src/content/blog/*.md` (frontmatter + markdown)
- **Route**: `src/pages/articles/[slug].astro` renders each article

## Linking to Articles

- Use `/articles/slug/` for internal links to articles (never `/blog/slug/`)
- Example: `[Related article](/articles/top-5-mistakes-to-avoid-when-mounting-your-tv/)`

## New Articles

When adding a new article:

1. Create `src/content/blog/your-article-slug.md` with frontmatter (title, description, pubDate, category, etc.)
2. The article will automatically be available at `/articles/your-article-slug/`
3. Add internal links using `/articles/` paths
4. The sitemap and redirects (blog→articles) are configured in `astro.config.mjs`
